data.title: moved
data.text: this deli is no longer at this location.  It has been gone for at least a year now. The food was good, service fine, but now gone. One location left, I believe it is in Benson.

data.title: Just Do It.
data.text: Absolutely worth stopping in. Local art is featured on the walls, the staff is pretty friendly, and the food is stupendous. Hands down the best sandwich I've eaten all year.

data.title: Great subs with hardroll that have great spices unique flavors
data.text: I'm tired of subway and this place is much bettter. They have a unique hard roll, with large sandwhices and great taste at around 6 to 9 bucks a sandwhich. Tired of subway? Try this place just off of 50th and saddlecreek.

data.title: Not Fast Food
data.text: I had heard rumblings about this place (as well as its newer sibling in Benson, across the street fromJake's), but had never tried it. I bought a groupon for Star awhile back, and with expiration approaching, today was the day. The inside is much nicer than the outside, with comfortable counters and booths, brightened. With showpiece art by locals. The menu gave a good choice of sandwiches, on your choice of bread. Mine was the meat and provolone on white baguette, with veggies and a light vinegar dressing. My wife chose the Cuban on wheat. Both were very tasty, and several levels ahead of the sandwiches most chains put out. All the ingredients were superior, especially the breads and veggies. Soups, a cream of asparagus and an onion, were both tasty as well ( although my asparagus soup could have been warmer). Speaking of warmer, it was cold inside, as both doors were propped open on a spring day in the 50s. We still don't know why. Service was friendly, but with only one person working, things moved a little lazily. A good place for excellent fare at reasonable prices--but give yourself time.

data.title: Very surprised
data.text: Ate at the Benson location because I was hungry and it was open and as a deli should be quick. The bread was fresh and good and the selection was great. Peach and pork was killer and the pulled pork was very tasty. Funky place, but don't be fooled!
